Terry,
The Win32 X-server approach seems to work fine.

The free copy can be downloaded from Starnet (home page: www.starnet.com,
evaluation download page: http://www.starnet.com/download/).
A version of the same server can be downloaded from:
ftp://ftp.informatik.uni-stuttgart.de/pub/SNNS/SNNSv4.1-Win32/X-Server/

Setting up the X-program:
1. Install the program the standard way.
2. Start up x-win32 to start the X server.
3. Click on x-util32 to configure a session.
4. In the window "X-win32 utility" click on "sessions" then on "new session."
5. Select connect using "rexec"
6. Put in session name (any name you like, e.g., "cortex") hostname
"cortex.spc.uchicago.edu" and your login name (account name)
7. Put in password if you want, but for safety you may want to leave this
blank.
8. Under "command" type "xterm -ls -display $DISPLAY"
9. Click on x-win32, select "sessions," then the session you created (e.g.,
"cortex")

Best wishes,
Stijn

